<h2><?php _e('Adding / Editing Levels', 'membership'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('You can add and / or edit levels using this form. Each level should have a unique title, the level shortcode is based on the title, so if a level title is too similar to another, it may be confusing when using the shortcodes to protect content at a later date.', 'membership'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Positive Rules', 'membership'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('A positive rule determines what content a user assigned to this level will have access to. To pick the content you should drag the relevant rules listed on the right hand side of the page to the DROP HERE box and then pick the content shown that you want the user to be able to access.', 'membership'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Negative Rules', 'membership'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('A negative rule determines what content a user assigned to this level will not have access to. To pick the content you should drag the relevant rules listed on the right hand side of the page to the DROP HERE box and then pick the content shown that you want to prevent the user from accessing.', 'membership'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Advanced (both)', 'membership'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('Sometimes you want to be able to use both positive and negative rules together, for example you may want to allow a user access to two pages, but not allow them access to a number of posts. You can accomplish this on the advanced tab by dragging the relevant rules to the appropriate DROP HERE boxes and selecting the content you want to allow / disallow access to.', 'membership'); ?></p>